#: ../../04_Data_presentation/Presentation_images.md:74
msgid "Each image needs a reference to its physical dimensions. This is typically achieved by including a scale bar with dimensions annotated in the image or the figure legend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_Data_presentation/Presentation_images.md:76
msgid "In addition, authors should remember to annotate the colors used, any symbols and arrows used to guide readers, and, if used, the origin of any zoom/inset. If specialized images are shown (time-lapse, volumes, reconstructions) authors are encouraged to consider annotating important information in the figures."
msgstr ""

